# Go Standards

All application code in this repository is **Go only**. Do not add Python, FastAPI, or pip/requirements.txt.

## Layout

```
go.mod                 # root module: github.com/therealagt/ContractManagementTool
services/api/cmd/      # service entrypoints (main packages)
services/api/internal/ # API-private packages (config, auth, db, routes)
services/*-worker/     # future workers: same cmd/ + internal/ pattern
libs/common/           # shared packages importable across services
```

- **No Python**: Remove or rewrite any `.py` files; never introduce new ones.
- **One module**: Single root `go.mod`. Services are packages under `services/`, not separate modules.
- **internal/**: HTTP handlers, middleware, and service wiring stay in `services/<name>/internal/`.
- **libs/common/**: Cross-service domain logic (audit, shared types) only — no HTTP or service wiring.

## Dependencies

- Prefer stdlib (`net/http`, `database/sql`, `context`, `encoding/json`).
- Routing: `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5`.
- PostgreSQL: `github.com/jackc/pgx/v5` (stdlib driver).
- Local dev DB: `modernc.org/sqlite` (no CGO).
- GCP IAP JWT: `google.golang.org/api/idtoken`.
- Pin versions in `go.mod`; run `go mod tidy` after changes.

## Style

- Small packages with clear names (`auth`, `config`, `db`, `audit`).
- Explicit error returns; wrap with `%w` when propagating.
- Fail closed on auth, validation, and signature checks — return proper HTTP status, never swallow errors.
- Config from environment variables (same names as Terraform/Cloud Run: `ENVIRONMENT`, `IAP_AUDIENCE`, etc.).
- Comments only for non-obvious compliance or regulatory intent.

## Patterns

```go
// BAD — silent failure on compliance gate
func upload(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    result, _ := validatePAdES(pdf)
    if result == nil {
        save(pdf)
    }
}

// GOOD — fail closed, auditable
result, err := validatePAdES(pdf)
if err != nil || !result.Valid {
    _ = audit.RecordAuditEvent(ctx, db, actor, "upload_rejected", &contractID, map[string]any{
        "reason": result.Error,
    }, nil)
    http.Error(w, "Invalid digital signature", http.StatusUnprocessableEntity)
    return
}
```

```go
// BAD — AI output treated as truth
saveMetadata(ctx, extracted)

// GOOD — draft until human confirms
saveExtractionDraft(ctx, extracted)
setStatus(ctx, contractID, "pending_review")
```

## Build & Deploy

- Local: `go run ./services/api/cmd/server`
- Docker: multi-stage build from repo root (`docker build -t contract-api .`; see root `Dockerfile`).
- Cloud Run listens on `:8080`; unauthenticated `/health` for probes.

## Do Not

- Add Python, Node backends, or alternate runtimes for services without explicit request.
- Put service-specific code in `libs/common/`.
- Use `panic` for expected errors (auth failures, validation, DB errors).
- Disable IAP, SoD, or HITL for convenience.
